ion hooks (log model load, each token, anomalies)\n110:- [ ] WS8-04 Interactive mode with streaming token output to TempleOS console\n111:- [ ] WS8-05 Performance tuning: identify and optimize top-5 hottest functions\n112:- [ ] WS8-06 Documentation: user guide for loading models and running inference\n118:- [ ] WS9-01 GPU threat model: DMA risks, firmware opacity, MMIO attack surface, IOMMU bypass vectors\n119:- [ ] WS9-02 IOMMU (VT-d/AMD-Vi) initialization and enforcement — mandatory, no GPU without it\n120:- [ ] WS9-03 GPU memory partition design — dedicated physical region, never overlaps kernel/log pages\n121:- [ ] WS9-04 Explicit copy-in/copy-out protocol — CPU copies tensors to GPU region, triggers compute, copies results\n122:- [ ] WS9-05 PCIe device enumeration in HolyC — discover GPU via config space, map BARs\n123:- [ ] WS9-06 GPU command submission interface — minimal ring buffer, no proprietary driver\n124:- [ ] WS9-07 MMIO register map for target GPU compute dispatch (start with virtio-gpu or simple compute)\n125:- [ ] WS9-08 Book of Truth hooks: log every DMA mapping, every GPU command, every MMIO write\n126:- [ ] WS9-09 GPU compute shader/kernel format — simple dispatachable compute tasks\n127:- [ ] WS9-10 Matmul offload: move quantized matrix multiply to GPU, keep results in GPU partition\n128:- [ ] WS9-11 Attention score computation offload to GPU\n129:- [ ] WS9-12 GPU error handling: timeout, hang detection, forced reset, logged to Book of Truth\n130:- [ ] WS9-13 Benchmark: GPU vs CPU inference speed for TinyLlama 1.1B Q4_0\n131:- [ ] WS9-14 Fallback: if no IOMMU available, GPU disabled entirely — CPU-only mode, no exceptions\n134:- [ ] WS10-01 Abstract forward pass interface — model-agnostic layer dispatch\n135:- [ ] WS10-02 Mistral architecture support (sliding window attention, different GQA config)\n136:- [ ] WS10-03 Qwen2 architecture support (different FFN layout, tied embeddings)\n137:- [ ] WS10-04 Phi-3 architecture support (different atten